
[1]silcia

   SI'LEX, SIL'CIA, n. One of the supposed primitive earths m usually
   found in the state of stone. When pure, it is perfectly white or
   colorless. The purer sorts are mountain crystal and quartz. Recent
   experiments prove this to be a compound substance, the base of which is
   a metal called silicium. Silica then is an oxyd of silicium.
